# RESP (Redis Serialization Protocol)

- Canonical spec: https://redis.io/docs/latest/develop/reference/protocol-spec/
- Support simple strings (`+`), errors (`-`), integers (`:`), bulk strings (`$`), and arrays (`*`).
- Lines end with CRLF (`\r\n`). Null bulk string is `$-1\r\n`.
- Add tests for examples such as `*1\r\n$4\r\nping\r\n`, `+OK\r\n`, and `$-1\r\n`.
